4.6.25  11:03 pm   Have you ever been working on a song and you have a temp vocal with words that don't necessarily make sense, but just fit the melody/rhythm of the vocal line.. but then, you wind up keeping some of those lyrics even if they don't really have a clear meaning? I've been working on this one song and I have this line in the temp vocals that goes "even in this old record town" and I really like the line. I don't know what the heck a 'record town' is or why I sang it at the time, but it really fits so well rhythmically/melodically and for some reason (though I can't pin it down) it even fits the feeling I'm trying to express in the song. I've tried playing with the words, maybe changing 'record' to wrecked up' or something... but "record town" just hits right and I feel like I need to keep it.
